<subSubSection id="C35F91F5FFDAFF86FCABFA6DFC1EF9AE" pageId="18" pageNumber="151" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFAC27EFFDAFF86FCABFA6DFC1EF9AE" blockId="18.[828,1437,190,1653]" pageId="18" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="B9311E6CFFDAFF86FCABFA6DFC13FA0E" bold="true" box="[828,959,1502,1525]" pageId="18" pageNumber="151">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is an adjective derived from the Sumerian name of the state that existed until the 6th century BC in the territory where the new species was found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
